main event: Two cigar-shaped, silver objects were seen in level flight over Big Rock Candy Mountain, Utah, on July 6, 1956.
interesting points: The objects were the size of a silver dollar at arm's length, one behind the other.
The objects disappeared behind the mountains.
The sighting lasted for only 10 seconds.
The report notes that the sighting was likely caused by aircraft.
The report mentions the description and sound of the objects, but does not provide any further details.
result: Likely caused by aircraft, though not definitively explained.
